        <h2>Background</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science from UC Berkeley, specializing in network communications, and spent nearly 20 years researching, studying, and lecturing at UC Berkeley&rsquo;s College of Engineering. At Nortel Networks (1996&ndash;2007), he served as Principal Scientist and Principal Architect, developing network management software for carrier-grade <a href="/communications-expert-witness/computer-networking-expert-witness/">network equipment</a> including <a href="/communications-expert-witness/routing-switching-expert/">routers, switches</a>, and <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-security-expert/">firewalls</a>. He also served as a DARPA Principal Investigator. Dr. Lavian has over 120 <a href="/patents/">patents</a> including innovations in network monitoring and device management, over 25 <a href="/scientific-publications/">scientific publications</a>, and has been retained in over 70 <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">cases</a>, including 80+ depositions, before U.S. federal courts, PTAB, ITC, and international tribunals.</p>

